  </div>
</div>

<!-- Stage 1: Serve Notice -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <div class="stage-card-header">
    <div class="stage-number">1</div>
    <div class="stage-title">
      <h2>Serve the Notice</h2>
      <div class="duration">Day 0 - Complete this stage first</div>
    </div>
    <span class="stage-status status-current">CURRENT</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stage-card-content">
    <div class="stage-grid">
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>What You Need to Do</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Print your notice (included in this pack)</li>
          <li>Serve via first-class post, recorded delivery, or hand delivery</li>
          <li>Complete the Proof of Service certificate</li>
          <li>Take photos/keep receipts as evidence</li>
          <li>Note exact date and time of service</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>Key Documents</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>{{notice_type}} (your notice)</li>
          <li>Service Instructions</li>
          <li>Proof of Service Certificate</li>
          <li>Witness statement (if hand-delivered)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tips-box">
      <strong>üí° Pro Tip:</strong> Hand delivery with a witness is the most secure method. Take a timestamped photo of the notice going through the letterbox.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Stage 2: Waiting Period -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <div class="stage-card-header">
    <div class="stage-number">2</div>
    <div class="stage-title">
      <h2>Notice Waiting Period</h2>
      <div class="duration">{{#if (eq notice_type "Section 8")}}14 days - 2 months (ground dependent){{else}}2 months minimum{{/if}}</div>
    </div>
    <span class="stage-status status-upcoming">UPCOMING</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stage-card-content">
    <div class="stage-grid">
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>During This Period</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Tenant should continue paying rent</li>
          <li>Keep records of all payments/non-payments</li>
          <li>Document any communications</li>
          <li>Prepare your court bundle</li>
          <li>Gather evidence (see Evidence Checklist)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>What to Expect</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Tenant may try to negotiate</li>
          <li>They may seek advice from CAB or shelter</li>
          <li>They might leave voluntarily (best outcome!)</li>
          <li>They might ignore the notice</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="warning-box">
      <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Important:</strong> Do NOT change locks, remove belongings, or harass the tenant. This is illegal eviction and could result in criminal charges against you.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Stage 3: File Court Claim -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <div class="stage-card-header">
    <div class="stage-number">3</div>
    <div class="stage-title">
      <h2>File Possession Claim</h2>
      <div class="duration">Court processing: 4-8 weeks</div>
    </div>
    <span class="stage-status status-upcoming">UPCOMING</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stage-card-content">
    <div class="stage-grid">
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>Filing Requirements</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Complete Form N5 (or N5B for accelerated)</li>
          <li>Complete Form N119 Particulars</li>
          <li>Pay court fee (¬£325-¬£355)</li>
          <li>Submit online (PCOL) or at local court</li>
          <li>Include copies of all evidence</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>What Happens Next</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Court sends claim to tenant</li>
          <li>Tenant has 14 days to respond</li>
          <li>Court allocates a hearing date</li>
          <li>You receive hearing notice by post</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tips-box">
      <strong>üí° Pro Tip:</strong> File online using Possession Claim Online (PCOL) at possessionclaim.gov.uk - it's faster and you can track progress.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Stage 4: Court Hearing -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <div class="stage-card-header">
    <div class="stage-number">4</div>
    <div class="stage-title">
      <h2>Court Hearing</h2>
      <div class="duration">Wait time: 8-16 weeks from filing</div>
    </div>
    <span class="stage-status status-upcoming">UPCOMING</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stage-card-content">
    <div class="stage-grid">
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>Preparing for Court</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Organize evidence bundle chronologically</li>
          <li>Number all pages</li>
          <li>Prepare 3 copies (court, tenant, yourself)</li>
          <li>Review your witness statement</li>
          <li>Know your arrears figures (if applicable)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>At the Hearing</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Arrive early (30 mins before)</li>
          <li>Dress smartly</li>
          <li>Bring all original documents</li>
          <li>Answer questions clearly and honestly</li>
          <li>Address the judge as "Sir/Madam" or "Your Honour"</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tips-box">
      <strong>üí° Pro Tip:</strong> If tenant doesn't attend or defend, you'll usually get a possession order. Section 21 accelerated claims often don't require a hearing at all.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Stage 5: Possession Order -->
<div class="stage-card">
  <div class="stage-card-header">
    <div class="stage-number">5</div>
    <div class="stage-title">
      <h2>Possession Order & Enforcement</h2>
      <div class="duration">2-6 weeks after hearing</div>
    </div>
    <span class="stage-status status-upcoming">UPCOMING</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stage-card-content">
    <div class="stage-grid">
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>If Tenant Leaves</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Conduct final inspection</li>
          <li>Complete inventory check</li>
          <li>Take photos of condition</li>
          <li>Return deposit (less deductions)</li>
          <li>Change locks and secure property</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-section">
        <h3>If Tenant Doesn't Leave</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Apply for warrant of possession</li>
          <li>Pay bailiff fee (¬£121-¬£130)</li>
          <li>Bailiff gives tenant eviction date</li>
          <li>Attend on eviction day</li>
          <li>Take back possession legally</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="warning-box">
      <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Never Self-Evict:</strong> Even with a possession order, you MUST use court bailiffs to physically evict. Changing locks yourself is still illegal.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

