<!-- Expert Tips -->
<div class="expert-tips">
  <div class="expert-tips-header">
    <span style="font-size: 16pt;">üí°</span>
    <h2>Expert Tips & Common Pitfalls</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="tip-grid">
    <div class="tip-card">
      <h4>‚úÖ Do: Keep Meticulous Records</h4>
      <p>Document everything. Courts love evidence. Keep copies of all letters, emails, texts, and payment records. A well-organized bundle wins cases.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card">
      <h4>‚úÖ Do: Communicate in Writing</h4>
      <p>Avoid phone calls where possible. Written communication (email/letter) creates a paper trail that can be used as evidence in court.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card warning">
      <h4>‚ùå Don't: Accept Partial Payments</h4>
      <p>If claiming rent arrears, be careful about accepting partial payments during proceedings. It can complicate your case. Get legal advice first.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card warning">
      <h4>‚ùå Don't: Make Verbal Agreements</h4>
      <p>Any agreement with the tenant should be in writing. Verbal promises to "move out next month" are worthless in court and reset your timeline.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

